meta {
  name: FCM Test Notification
  type: http
  seq: 3
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/push/fcm-test
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{token}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "title": "🔔 Test Notification",
    "body": "This is a test notification from RTS."
  }
}

script:post-response {
  if (res.status === 200 && res.body.success) {
    console.log(`✅ Notification sent to ${res.body.tokenCount} device(s)`);
  } else if (res.status === 404) {
    console.log("❌ No FCM tokens registered for this user — Flutter app must call /fcm-register first");
  } else if (res.status === 403) {
    console.log("❌ SuperUser only");
  } else if (res.status === 400) {
    console.log("❌ Validation error:", res.body.error);
  } else {
    console.log("❌", res.body.error);
  }
}

docs {
  # FCM Test Notification (SuperUser only)

  Sends a test FCM push notification to a specific user's registered mobile devices.
  Use this to verify the full notification pipeline end-to-end without triggering a real event.

  ## Testing steps
  1. Log into the Flutter app on a real device (emulators may not receive FCM).
  2. Flutter calls POST /push/fcm-register with the FCM token after login.
  3. Run this request from Bruno (logged in as SuperUser).
  4. Notification should appear on the device within a few seconds.
  5. Tap the notification — the app should open request details directly (deep link).

  ## Access
  Any authenticated user — sends to your own devices by default.
  SuperUser / Admin can pass `empId` to test any user's device.

  ## Body fields
  | Field | Required | Default                              | Description                              |
  |-------|----------|--------------------------------------|------------------------------------------|
  | empId | no       | caller's own empId                   | Target user (SuperUser/Admin only)       |
  | title | no       | "🔔 Test Notification"               | Notification title                       |
  | body  | no       | "This is a test notification..."     | Notification body text                   |

  ## FCM data payload received by mobile app
  All new-request notifications include these fields in the FCM `data` map:

  | Field        | Type   | Example value                                          | Notes                                    |
  |--------------|--------|--------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------|
  | `type`       | string | `"new_request"`                                        | Notification category                    |
  | `request_id` | string | `"232"`                                                | Parse to int, navigate to this request   |
  | `deepLink`   | string | `"http://192.168.1.128:5173/?openRequest=232"`         | Full URL for WebView or in-app browser   |
  | `url`        | string | `"/?openRequest=232"`                                  | Relative URL (used by web service worker)|
  | `tag`        | string | `"request-232"`                                        | Notification dedup tag                   |
  | `action`     | string | `"new_request"`                                        | Action identifier                        |
  | `channel_id` | string | `"new_request_channel"`                                | Android notification channel             |

  ## Deep link handling (Flutter)
  On notification tap, read `data['request_id']` and navigate to the request detail screen:
  ```dart
  final requestId = int.tryParse(message.data['request_id'] ?? '');
  if (requestId != null) {
    Navigator.push(context, MaterialPageRoute(
      builder: (_) => RequestDetailScreen(requestId: requestId),
    ));
  }
  ```
  Alternatively use `data['deepLink']` to open via in-app WebView.

  ## Response
  ```json
  { "success": true, "tokenCount": 1 }
  ```
  `tokenCount` tells you how many devices the notification was sent to.

  ## Errors
  - **400** — `empId` missing
  - **403** — caller is not SuperUser
  - **404** — user has no registered FCM tokens (Flutter hasn't called /fcm-register yet)
}
